Native American Grebe Gods and Spirits
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b>Shingebiss</b> (Ojibwe)<BR>

<H2><U>
Native American Legends About Grebes
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.mpm.edu/wirp/ICW-141.html#winter
">The Helldiver and the Spirit of Winter</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Chippewa Indian legend about a brave grebe withstanding winter's fury.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.mpm.edu/wirp/ICW-141.html#geese
">Wenebojo and the Dancing Geese</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.ucan-online.org/legend.asp?legend=5143&category=7
">Manabozho and the Hell-Diver</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.mpm.edu/wirp/ICW-138.html#birds
">Manabush and the Birds</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/TheShut-EyeDance-Menomini.html
">The Shut-Eye Dance</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.calverley.ca/Part06-Legends/6-009.html
">Weesakaychuk and the Ducks</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Algonquian legends telling how Grebe got his strange appearance.
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Grebe Stories from Native American Myth and Legend
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0472106112/natilangofthe-20
">Birds of Algonquin Legend</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Interesting collection of legends about grebes and other birds in Algonquian tribes.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1555911277/natilangofthe-20
">Native American Animal Stories</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Great collection of American Indian tales about animals, told by Abenaki storyteller Joseph Bruchac. 
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0385342489/natilangofthe-20
">Flights of Fancy: Birds in Myth, Legend, and Superstition</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A good book on the symbolism of birds in world mythology, including North and South America.
<BR>




